malignant.英释: a malignant disease is one such as  cancer  , which can develop in an uncontrolled way and is likely to cause someone’s death

monstrous.中释: 巨大的；恐怖的；可耻的，丢脸的

alternate.英释: if two things alternate, or if you alternate them, they happen one after the other in a repeated pattern

establish.中释: 建立，委任；安置；证实；确立
establish.英释: to start a company, organization, system, etc that is intended to exist or continue for a long time

rectangle.英释: a shape that has four straight sides, two of which are usually longer than the other two, and four 90˚ angles at the corners

pesticide.英释: a chemical substance used to kill insects and small animals that destroy crops

municipal.英释: relating to or belonging to the government of a town or city

clockwise.英释: in the same direction as the  hands  of a clock move

speculate.英释: to guess about the possible causes or effects of something, without knowing all the facts or details

volunteer.英释: someone who does a job willingly without being paid

implement.英释: to take action or make changes that you have officially decided should happen

propagate.英释: to spread an idea, belief etc to many people

semblance.英释: If there is a semblance of a particular condition or quality, it appears to exist, even though this may be a false impression

ingenious.中释: 机灵的；制作精巧的，灵巧的
ingenious.英释: an ingenious plan, idea, or object works well and is the result of clever thinking and new ideas

procedure.英释: a way of doing something, especially the correct or usual way

reference.英释: a number that tells you where you can find the information you want in a book, on a map etc

eccentric.中释: 古怪(的)，偏执(的)，不同心(的)
eccentric.英释: An eccentric is an eccentric person

obstinate.中释: 顽固的，倔强的，不易屈服的，较难治愈的
obstinate.英释: determined not to change your ideas, behaviour, opinions etc, even when other people think you are being unreasonable

Christian.英释: a person who believes in the ideas taught by Jesus Christ

strategic.英释: done as part of a plan, especially in a military, business, or political situation

melodious.英释: something that sounds melodious sounds like music or has a pleasant tune

commodity.英释: a product that is bought and sold

intensify.英释: to increase in degree or strength, or to make something do this

escalator.英释: a set of moving stairs that take people to different levels in a building

collision.英释: an accident in which two or more people or vehicles hit each other while moving in different directions

intervene.中释: 插入，介入，干涉，(时间)介于
intervene.英释: to become involved in an argument, fight, or other difficult situation in order to change what happens

lucrative.英释: a job or activity that is lucrative lets you earn a lot of money

elsewhere.英释: in, at, or to another place

monologue.英释: a long speech by one person

identical.英释: exactly the same, or very similar

withstand.英释: If something or someone withstands a force or action, they survive it or do not give in to it

pollinate.英释: to give a flower or plant pollen so that it can produce seeds

affection.英释: If you regard someone or something with affection, you like them and are fond of them

publicity.英释: Publicity is information or actions that are intended to attract the public's attention to someone or something

inflation.英释: a continuing increase in prices, or the rate at which prices increase

platitude.英释: a statement that has been made many times before and is not interesting or clever – used to show disapproval

incentive.英释: something that encourages you to work harder, start a new activity etc

literally.英释: You can use literally to emphasize an exaggeration. Some careful speakers of English think that this use is incorrect.

paralysis.英释: the loss of the ability to move all or part of your body or feel things in it

safeguard.英释: to protect something from harm or damage

spectator.英释: someone who is watching an event or game

indemnity.英释: protection against loss or damage, especially in the form of a promise to pay for any losses or damage

exclusive.中释: 孤傲的；不愿吸收新会员的；索价高昂的
exclusive.英释: exclusive places, organizations, clothes etc are so expensive that not many people can afford to use or buy them

intricate.英释: containing many small parts or details that all work or fit together

available.英释: something that is available is able to be used or can easily be bought or found

cultivate.英释: to prepare and use land for growing crops and plants

pragmatic.英释: dealing with problems in a sensible practical way instead of strictly following a set of ideas

sensitive.中释: 敏感的；过敏的，容易生气的；仪器灵敏的
sensitive.英释: easily upset or offended by events or things that people say

segregate.英释: to separate one group of people from others, especially because they are of a different race, sex, or religion

surcharge.英释: money that you have to pay in addition to the basic price of something

democracy.中释: 民主，民主政体，民主社会
democracy.英释: a system of government in which every citizen in the country can vote to elect its government officials

indicator.英释: something that can be regarded as a sign of something else

persevere.英释: to continue trying to do something in a very determined way in spite of difficulties – use this to show approval

marvelous.中释: 令人惊奇的；创造奇迹的

hierarchy.英释: a system of organization in which people or things are divided into levels of importance

artillery.英释: Artillery consists of large, powerful guns that are transported on wheels and used by an army

ventilate.英释: to let fresh air into a room, building etc

coalition.英释: a union of two or more political parties that allows them to form a government or fight an election together
